  "body": "I'm working on a project with KYC requirements and am considering overriding the ability for the purchase to be from an address other than the token receiver.\r\n\r\nBefore I override I wanted to check to be certain there's nothing important I'm missing. Does anyone know the motivation behind making the low level buyTokens method public? If I were to override and make it private, or otherwise remove the ability to send ETH from one address and receive tokens at another, are there important considerations that I'm missing?\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/OpenZeppelin/zeppelin-solidity/blob/master/contracts/crowdsale/Crowdsale.sol#L69 ",
