    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "We separated the purchasing address from the beneficiary address to allow the creation of software that buys tokens for others. For example, a chrome extension that receives eth funds, crafts a purchase transaction, but gives the tokens to the original sender of funds. \r\nThis is also needed for any other use-case where the one sending the money is not the one that should receive the tokens.",
